                  </hi>. I am shop-boy to Mr. Matthews. I remember the pri<lb></lb>soner bringing these wheels—I am sure he is the person—I went with the policeman and pointed him out.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430612-name-1475" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1475" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1475" type="surname" value="WOOD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1475" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY WOOD</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable K</hi> 44.) Easton pointed out the prisoner to me—I asked where he got those wheels—he said he never sold any wheels to him; but at the station he said, "I will pay the money sooner than go before the Magistrate."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> From last August I was at work; I know nothing about the wheels; if I had wanted to sell them, I should not have gone close to my own home; there are plenty of men dressed like me.</p>
